identificationModule.briefTitle: HepB mAb19 in Individuals With Chronic Hepatitis B Infection
identificationModule.officialTitle: A Phase 1, Placebo-controlled, Dose-escalation Study of the Safety, Pharmacokinetics, and Antiviral Activity of a Potent Neutralizing Monoclonal Antibody in Individuals With Chronic Hepatitis B Infection

descriptionModule.briefSummary: This is a first-in-human, placebo-controlled, single dose, dose-escalation phase 1 study to evaluate the safety, pharmacokinetics and antiviral activity of a highly potent neutralizing anti-HBV monoclonal antibody (mAb), HepB mAb19, which targets the S-protein in individuals with chronic hepatitis B (CHB) on nucleos(t)ide analog therapy (NRTI).
descriptionModule.detailedDescription: The study has a dose escalation design. In Groups 1-4, eligible participants will be randomized at a 3:1 ratio to receive a single intravenous infusion of HepB mAb19 or placebo (normal saline) at one of four increasing dose levels (1 mg/kg, 3 mg/kg, 10 mg/kg and 30 mg/kg). In Group 5 participants will receive HepB mAb19 at the maximum tolerated dose (MTD). Participants will be followed for 48 weeks after HepB mAb19 or placebo infusion.

interventions.name: HepB mAb19
interventions.description: HepB mAb19 is a human mAb of IgG1kappa isotype that specifically binds to the "a" determinant of the extracellular loop of the HBV surface antigen (HBsAg).

interventions.name: Sterile Saline
interventions.description: Placebo will be normal sterile saline (NaCl 0.9%).

primaryOutcomes.measure: Rate and severity of solicited adverse events that are Grade 2 or above within 2 weeks after administration.
primaryOutcomes.description: The occurrence of solicited AEs will be assessed 2 weeks after IP administration.

primaryOutcomes.measure: Rate and severity of treatment-emerging unsolicited adverse events that are Grade 2 or above (including confirmed laboratory abnormalities) within 2, 12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration.
primaryOutcomes.description: The occurrence of treatment-emerging AEs will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Rate and severity of participants with serious adverse events (SAEs) throughout the study period that are considered related to investigational product and the duration of those SAEs.
primaryOutcomes.description: The occurrence of SAEs will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Rate and severity of participants with potential immune complex disease (ICD) throughout the study period following investigational product (IP) administration.
primaryOutcomes.description: The occurrence of immune complex disease will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in AST within 2,12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration.
primaryOutcomes.description: Changes in AST will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in ALT within 2,12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration
primaryOutcomes.description: Changes in ALT will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in alkaline phosphatase within 2,12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration
primaryOutcomes.description: Changes in alkaline phosphatase will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in bilirubin within 2,12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration
primaryOutcomes.description: Changes in bilirubin will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in albumin within 2,12, 24 and 48 weeks after administration
primaryOutcomes.description: Changes in albumin will be assessed after IP administration
Elimination half-life (t1/2) will be assessed after IP administration
Clearance (CL/F) will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Volume of Distribution (Vz/F) of HepB mAb19
primaryOutcomes.description: Volume of Distribution (Vz/F) will be assessed after IP administration

primaryOutcomes.measure: Area under the curve (AUC) of HepB mAb19
primaryOutcomes.description: Area under the curve (AUC) will be assessed after IP administration
Decay Curve will be assessed after IP administration

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate and severity of treatment-related adverse events during study follow up.
secondaryOutcomes.description: The occurrence of treatment-related AEs will be assessed after IP administration.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of induced anti-HepB mAb19 antibodies in all study groups.
secondaryOutcomes.description: Occurrence of anti-HepB mAb19 antibodies will be assessed at baseline and after IP administration.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Change in quantitative HBsAg levels from baseline (day 0) at each scheduled follow up visit.
secondaryOutcomes.description: Serum HBsAg levels will be measured from baseline (day 0) until end of study follow up.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Detection of HBsAg by a qualitative assay at each scheduled follow up visit.
secondaryOutcomes.description: Qualitative measure of HBsAg will be performed from baseline (day 0) until end of study follow up.
